If you create policy.json in ~/.config/containers/policy.json
Something like:
```{
    "default": [
        {
            "type": "insecureAcceptAnything"
        }
    ],
    "transports":
        {
            "docker-daemon":
                {
                    "": [{"type":"insecureAcceptAnything"}]
                }
        }
}
```

Does it work?

@rhatdan, I removed the assigned from me. 

I think the request should be discussed in a bigger round. There are many configuration files that "could" be passed around and I am not sure we want to expose all of them in the Podman flags.

If we do that, I'd vote for making them root-level flags (e..g, podman --conf) instead of adding them to each and every command that may need them.

